ce:section.ce:para:
The optimized structure of adsorbed CO2 shows no significant changes in the O-C-O bond angle compared to that of the isolated CO2. However, a slight change is seen in the bond length of the C-O bond of CO2* (+0.02 Å), connected to the Fe atom, compared to isolated CO2 molecule which implies a weakening of the C-O bond since the elongation of 0.02 Å is significant in the C = O rigid double bond. Following the adsorption of CO₂ onto the catalyst, the NBO charge of Fe changes from +0.85e to +0.60e which indicates the charge transfer from the HOMO of the CO₂ (lone electron pairs of O atom and π electrons of the C = O bond) to the empty d orbitals of Fe site. The calculated orbital interaction energies (E 
                           (2)) for the (nO
                            —>dFe
                           ) and (πC-O
                            —>dFe
                           ) are 47.64 and 8.26 kcal/mol, respectively. These charge transfers make [CO2]δ+species which drive the reaction.
